WRITING.TEXT: Good evening community, ------------------- since in the long run the 3D printing in your own room is harmful, I am searching for ideas to manufacture an enclosure. ----------------------------------------------- There are some requirements: ------------------------------- 1. WRITING.TEXT: I went through a psych evaluation. Psychological Report: Current complaints: The patient has the experience of preferring not to trust others. So he has a good friend next to the family and withdraw very socially. He had already noticed these schizoid behaviors in his childhood, so he is better off as a loner. Due to racist mobbing experiences in his childhood from his teachers, the patient tries to process his trauma through hours of video games. Sometimes he even hears the voice of his teachers. Moreover, the patient insists that he does not understand society itself and its sin. #8203; According to clinical findings, the affected one suffers from a moderate recurrent depressive epidermis. In addition, the patient suffers from the social and emotional effects of his schizoid personality accentuation. #8203; My toughts: Due to my family education, I do not try to put someone in a pigeonhole fig. However, I have always painfully realized that selfish ulterior motives cause people to hurt each other. To study, I have moved far away to leave the problems behind me. Actually, I am even a social person and would be happy to help other people as well. The problem is that whenever I encounter rejection, my old thoughts recur again. I'm sad, but also very angry, because society does not do much about it and even some people negate the problem. But maybe I was too naive and think too romantic. Can someone please help me? :)

WRITING.TITLE: I love doing bouldering
WRITING.TEXT: In the past couple of months I set the goal to loose weight. I ate 1500kcal per day and started going to run on my own. After some time I started with calisthenics in order to build some muscel too. And then I tought what should I do with muscels if I even dont know how to use them? So I tryed Kravmaga, Karate and Kendo. I got ennoyed by the fact that in order to do this kind of sports for a longer period of time, that you have to build deeper relationships with others. So I quit all of them. By coincidence I found out about bouldering. It is completely different from the other sports. 1. You dont need someone to climb a wall. 2. The bouldering community is very kind. 3. You will see everty time new people and non of them will try to force you to talk with them. 4. And if we talk we mostly talk about how to climb up the spesific level. 5. Your can start at any condition 6. Your body will adapt and transform. It is now 3 months since I started with the goal to loose weight. I lost about 11kgs ~ 24.2 lbs and my bmi is 24. I took pictures every day and my body changed a lot. You can ask me if you have any questions.
